From 795316fdc460155fdaa98689901e1a1cca4e5238 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 16:56:07 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 041/174] =?UTF-8?q?PGCL:=20alpha/mips64/microblaze/hppa=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?fixes=20=E2=80=94=2015=20arches=20boot,=20expanded=20test=20sui?=
 =?UTF-8?q?te?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Alpha: copy_page/clear_page assembly had hardcoded 8KB (MMUPAGE_SIZE) loop
counts instead of using PAGE_SIZE/64. With MMUSHIFT=4 (PAGE_SIZE=128KB),
only 8KB was copied/cleared, corrupting page contents. Fixed all 4 assembly
files (copy_page.S, ev6-copy_page.S, clear_page.S, ev6-clear_page.S).

MIPS64: Complete PGCL support — page table geometry (PGDIR_SHIFT, PMD_SHIFT,
PTRS_PER_* all use MMUPAGE_SHIFT), PFN encoding (__phys_to_pte_val two-step
shift to handle PFN_PTE_SHIFT != MMUPAGE_SHIFT), _PFN_MASK sub-page bits,
set_ptes PGCL sub-page loop, TLB flush stride (5 functions PAGE→MMUPAGE),
flush_cache_page MMUPAGE_MASK, PM_DEFAULT_MASK uses CONFIG_PAGE_SHIFT.

Microblaze: hw_exception_handler.S used PAGE_SIZE/PAGE_MASK for page table
walks in data storage, data TLB miss, and instruction TLB miss handlers.
With MMUSHIFT=4, wrong masks caused PGD/PTE lookups to fail on write faults.
Fixed 12 instances across 3 handlers + finish_tlb_load. Also fixed pgtable.h,
head.S, pgtable.c for MMUPAGE alignment, and updated system.dts for QEMU.

hppa: entry.S L2_ptep macro used PAGE_SHIFT to clear offset bits in page
directory pointer instead of ASM_PLD_SHIFT (MMUPAGE_SHIFT). Page directory
tables are MMUPAGE-sized, so wrong masking truncated pointer causing infinite
TLB miss loops. Fixes both hppa32 and hppa64.

powerpc: Minor mmap2 pgoff shift fix in syscalls.c.

Test results with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4:
- x86_64:      19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP), mm-selftests PASS
- arm64:       19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP), mm-selftests PASS
- riscv64:     19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP), mm-selftests PASS
- ppc64:       19/19 pgcl-test, 13/13 pgcl-stress, mm-selftests PASS
- s390x:       19/19 pgcl-test, 13/13 pgcl-stress, mm-selftests PASS
- sparc64:     19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP), mm-selftests PASS
- arm32:       19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP), mm-selftests PASS
- alpha:       19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP)
- loongarch64: 19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP)
- mips64:      19/19 pgcl-test, 11/11 pgcl-stress (2 SKIP)
- hppa32:      19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP)
- hppa64:      19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP)
- riscv32:     19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP)
- m68k:        19/19 pgcl-test, 12/12 pgcl-stress (1 SKIP)

